Cups-browsed unit tests require running avahi-daemon and NSS mdns setup. Both steps need root. We don't want to do this on build machines, so automatic tests are disabled by default.

Follow these steps to run the tests by hand on your personal machine:
1. Log into a VM machine, ex. virtual.cz or virtuals.cz.
2. vm create ST_userland_build cups-browsed
3. vm start cups-browsed
4. vm ssh cups-browsed
5. Complete the instructions it gaves you in motd.
6. sudo svcadm enable network/dns/multicast
7. sudo svccfg -s svc:/system/name-service/switch
8. setprop config/host = astring: "files mdns dns"
9. select system/name-service/switch:default
10. refresh
11. quit
12. cd /scratch/userland-gate/components/openprinting/cups-browsed && gmake publish
13. (build/amd64; /usr/bin/env /usr/gnu/bin/make check)

All tests must PASS.
